    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka records first passport baby after woman goes into labour at emigration queue",
      "author": "Neshella Perera",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT- A 26-year-old pregnant woman in line with her husband to get her passport from Sri Lanka\u2019s Department of Immigration and Emigration had gone into labor.",
        "Chandra Krishnan, the Officer at the Department of Immigration and Emigration told EconomyNext on Thursday July 07 that the couple had been in the queue since last night waiting to obtain their passports.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s Immigration and Emigration Department has seen in a significant increase in new passports issued, with 31,725 passports issued in the first 10 days of June alone, a threefold increase.",
        "Many have resorted to fleeing the country due to Sri Lanka\u2019s worsening economic crisis, with exorbitant price increments and scarcity of essentials going making life increasingly hard to the middle classes and below.",
        "Crisit-hit Sri Lanka sees unusual spike in new passports issued",
        "Thursday morning, when the pregnant woman had gone to the washroom, she had felt her labour pains and shouted for help when female army officers had rushed to help and called for a wheelchair.",
        "\u201cShe had got the pains at 7.40 and was transported immediately to Colombo Castle Hospital. The baby was delivered on admission to hospital. She gave birth to a baby girl,\u201d\u00a0 said Krishan.",
        "Media Spokesperson of the Army Nilantha Premaratne told EconomyNext that the couple was from Hatton and this was their first born, adding that both mother and baby are safe. (Colombo/Jul07/2022)"
      ],
